    prov:actedOnBehalfOf <https://www.linkedin.com/in/kidehen#this> .

:a1 a schema:Answer ;
    schema:text "Blitzscaling, from Reid Hoffman and Chris Yeh's book, prioritizes speed of growth over operational efficiency on the assumption efficiency can be retrofitted after scale is captured. Ilya Sutskever's framing of brute-force compute scaling as 'low-risk' mirrors this logic applied to model training."@en .

:a10 a schema:Answer ;
    schema:text "A tiny recursive model that solves logic problems without massive-scale training, winning a $50,000 prize and showing that genuinely efficient alternatives to brute-force scaling exist."@en .

:a11 a schema:Answer ;
    schema:text "Hoffman describes blitzscaling as 'assembling a plane while falling.' Applied to AI, vague 'compute multiplier' efficiency claims mean the trillion-dollar bet cannot retrofit efficiency later if capital access tightens — the bubble-risk scenario."@en .

:a12 a schema:Answer ;
    schema:text "Bundling (de-monetizing competitors by folding a capability into an existing platform) and open-sourcing (commoditizing a layer while preserving value in a service built atop it). DeepSeek's commodity-hardware, low-cost approach escapes both, forcing market-wide commoditization instead."@en .

:a2 a schema:Answer ;
    schema:text "Blitzscaling normally works because scale lowers unit cost through network effects. Large language models scale quadratically, not logarithmically — each added parameter costs more, not less — inverting the returns blitzscaling depends on."@en .

:a3 a schema:Answer ;
    schema:text "Onto the shared computing market: AI firms may be purchasing 70% of the world's high-end memory supply, hard-drive prices rose from $350 to $800 in two years, and US data-center capacity is being expanded roughly eightfold."@en .

:a4 a schema:Answer ;
    schema:text "Approximately $226.5 billion — more than five times its reported long-term debt of $43.2 billion — driven substantially by AI infrastructure commitments."@en .

:a5 a schema:Answer ;
    schema:text "Roughly 45% of Microsoft's $625 billion commercial backlog traces to a single customer, OpenAI, which has never generated a profit and is projected to burn $12-15 billion in 2026 operating losses."@en .

:a6 a schema:Answer ;
    schema:text "Not capital and not demand, but electricity — the grid constraint that no amount of capex can solve, per the Microsoft forensic analysis."@en .

:a7 a schema:Answer ;
    schema:text "Nvidia's single-day loss of $593 billion, the largest in US equity history, following the shock of DeepSeek's comparably capable model built on commodity hardware at a fraction of the cost."@en .

:a8 a schema:Answer ;
    schema:text "As the predictable 'scale-out' commoditization phase that follows every 'scale-up' technology cycle — mainframe to mini to micro to mobile, big iron to distributed computing to internet — with hyperscalers missing it because massive capex aligned with their existing cloud infrastructure rather than because it was the smartest path."@en .

:a9 a schema:Answer ;
    schema:text "Google, Meta, Microsoft-OpenAI, and xAI optimized within their existing constraints — cloud infrastructure they already owned — rather than questioning whether the scale-up model itself was the right bet."@en .

:alexReisner a schema:Person ;
    schema:name "Alex Reisner"@en .

:q1 a schema:Question ;
    schema:acceptedAnswer :a1 ;
    schema:isPartOf :faqSection ;
    schema:name "What is blitzscaling, and how does it apply to frontier AI labs?"@en .

:q10 a schema:Question ;
    schema:acceptedAnswer :a10 ;
    schema:isPartOf :faqSection ;
    schema:name "What did Microsoft researcher Alexia Jolicoeur-Martineau demonstrate as an alternative?"@en .

:q11 a schema:Question ;
    schema:acceptedAnswer :a11 ;
    schema:isPartOf :faqSection ;
    schema:name "What is blitzscaling's own stated failure mode, and why does it matter here?"@en .

:q12 a schema:Question ;
    schema:acceptedAnswer :a12 ;
    schema:isPartOf :faqSection ;
    schema:name "What are the two traditional hyperscaler strategies DeepSeek escapes?"@en .

:q2 a schema:Question ;
    schema:acceptedAnswer :a2 ;
    schema:isPartOf :faqSection ;
    schema:name "Why does quadratic LLM scaling break the blitzscaling playbook?"@en .

:q3 a schema:Question ;
    schema:acceptedAnswer :a3 ;
    schema:isPartOf :faqSection ;
    schema:name "Where does the externalized cost of the scaling bet land?"@en .

